Description: Body sherd of black-figured North Ionian pottery vessel, perhaps amphora; interior reserved; exterior white slip: two pairs of horses' (?) forelegs to left; meander band below.
Curator's comments: From same vase as B103.3 (GR 1888.6-1.460. i) with several pairs of horses’ legs and B103.7 (GR 1888.6-1.539f) with heads of two horses. Very close, probably same vase is Oxford, Ashmolean Museum AN1912.33b.
Bibliographic references: Vase / Catalogue of Vases in the British Museum (B103.4.3)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.966)
